HEADWORD: Biliverdin
<hw>Bil`i*ver"din</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>bilis</ets> bile + <ets>viridis</ets> green. Cf.
<er>Verdure</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>A green pigment
present in the bile, formed from bilirubin by oxidation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

